  "texts": [
    "Instead of simply cascading stages, the architecture integrates a supervised attention block between stages, which facilitates progressive learning and preserves important spectral details (Zamir et al. 2021).",
    "The first two stages utilize an encoderdecoder structure, preparing the groundwork for detailed reconstruction.",
    "The final stage combines the original input with the enhanced image from the second stage, using a special-ized Original Resolution Subnetwork (ORSNet) that maintains the original image's resolution.",
    "This approach allows MPRNet to merge the detailed aspects of the original image with the improvements from earlier stages, resulting in a highly refined final output.",
    "where, l char = Charbonnier loss, l edge = Edge loss, X s = Restored image, Y = Ground truth image."
  ],
